# Mindbrain Memory

This project uses Mindbrain for persistent memory across sessions.

## Commands

- `mb context -f <files> -t "<task>"` — Recall relevant past knowledge
- `mb save "<title>" -t <type>` — Save a note (user|feedback|project|reference|codebase|debug)
- `mb search "<query>"` — Search notes
- `mb mine --dry-run` — Extract notes from past conversations

## Workflow

1. **Start of session**: Run `mb context -f <current files> -t "<what you're doing>"` to load relevant memories
2. **User corrects you**: `mb save "correction description" -t feedback`
3. **Bug resolved**: `mb save "bug description and fix" -t debug`
4. **Architecture decision**: `mb save "decision description" -t project`
